<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870702-0079 </DOCNO><HL> Niagara Mohawk GetsFull-Power PermissionFor Nine Mile 2 Plant</HL><DD> 07/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NMK LIL CNH NGE RGS GOVMTNUCLEAR POWER, FUEL (NUK)UTILITIES (UTI) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Nuclear Regulatory Commission voted 4-0 to allow Niagara Mohawk Power Corp. to operate at full power the Nine Mile 2 nuclear power plant near Oswego, N.Y.    Niagara Mohawk, Syracuse, N.Y., owns 41% of the plant; Long Island Lighting Co. and New York State Electric andamp; Gas Corp. each owns 18%; Rochester Gas andamp; Electric Corp. has a 14% stake, and Central Hudson Gas andamp; Electric Corp.'s stake is 9%.    Niagara Mohawk's president, William Donlon, said the company plans to have the unit in full commercial operation by December or early next year.    A Niagara Mohawk spokesman said the financing costs attributed to the Nine Mile 2 plant &quot;have already been incorporated in consumer electric rates.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>